--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Overview
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I am ostensibly building a C compiler.  This project started out as a simple
lexer, but I've moved beyond that and am now dabbling in parsing.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Setup, Requirements, Etc.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Setup:

> cd /path/to/project/root
> source env/shell

Build:

> build

Run:

> run --help

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Overview
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
gs.h is my own "standard" library. I'm maintaining that elsewhere.

gstest.h and test.c are used for testing the lexer and parser. gstest.h is the
testing portion to gs.h.

sample.c and test.c are test inputs to throw at the lexer and parser.

Of primary concern for anyone reading this are the files: main.c, lexer.c and
parser.c.

